1 NOTE Obit for Roseanna Reinsel<br><br>     Death`s Doings<br>We are sorry tonote the 
2 CONC death of Mrs. Jonathan Reinsel, of RedbankTownship, Whichoccurred on last Satu r
2 CONC day night. The deceased was in herusual healthduring the day and read the pape r
2 CONC s and chatted with thefamily in theevening. She retired a little before ten o` c
2 CONC lock. Aboutmid-nightshe gotup, lit the lamp and told her husband she was getti n
2 CONC gone of her chockingspells. In about 15 minutes she was dead.<br>She was the d a
2 CONC ughter ofDaniel Aaron, one of the first settlers ofLimestone township. A broth e
2 CONC r, D.H. Aaron of Redbank township and asister, Mrs Daniel English ofPittsburg h 
2 CONC are the only ones of a largefamily to survive her. Besidesher husband she lea ve
2 CONC s to morn their lossnine children, three sons andsix daughters. The sons are Edw
2 CONC ard and D.L.Reinsel of Crates and John. Tof Clarion. The daughters are Mrs. Will
2 CONC iamWeaver, Mrs. John E. Aaron,Mrs. P. F. Fiscus, and Laura, Cora and Emmawh o ar
2 CONC e still at home. Thedeceased was about 65 years of age. Thefuneral took pla ce a
2 CONC t St.Nicholas church at Crates, on Tuesday at 10o`clock., Rev. Ruddy officiating
2 CONC .
