1 NOTE Robert "Bob" Carl Allison, 89, died on Sunday, October 27, 2019, surrounded by h
2 CONC is family at West Penn Hospital in Pittsburgh.<br><br>Born October 8, 1930 on th
2 CONC e family homestead in Limestone, he was the son of Roy Carl and Daisy Mabel (Mon
2 CONC g) Allison.<br><br>Mr. Allison graduated from Clarion-Limestone High School in 1
2 CONC 948 and Pennsylvania State University in 1952 with a degree in Agricultural Scie
2 CONC nces.<br><br>He met the love of his life, Margaret "Peggy" Therese Reinsel, in h
2 CONC igh school when they sat next to one another in class. In 10th grade, he was ask
2 CONC ed to a Sadie Hawkins dance by Peggy for their first date. On Thanksgiving, Nove
2 CONC mber 22, 1951, Bob and Peggy married at the St. Nicholas Catholic Church in Crat
2 CONC es.<br><br>Mr. Allison was renowned for his hard work and dedication to his fami
2 CONC ly throughout his life. After serving in the Army, he was an agricultural extens
2 CONC ion agent in Washington and Butler counties.<br><br>He and Peggy returned to Cla
2 CONC rion County, where they raised their family and lived for the rest of their live
2 CONC s.<br><br>Mr. Allison was deeply tied to his family heritage in the Limestone ar
2 CONC ea and the Allison homestead which was settled in 1802 by his great-great-grandf
2 CONC ather.<br><br>In addition to farming, he also taught vocational-agriculture at C
2 CONC larion-Limestone and Redbank Valley.<br><br>Mr. Allison owned and operated a tru
2 CONC cking company for several years and was a partner and founder of Limestone Gas.<
2 CONC br><br>He continued to be lifelong farmer. Late in his life, he could still be f
2 CONC ound roaming the fields "supervising" the work.<br><br>Mr. Allison loved to exhi
2 CONC bit his restored 1938 John Deere G at local tractor shows, bringing home many tr
2 CONC ophies.<br><br>Jokes, laughter, wit and wisdom were an integral part of Mr. Alli
2 CONC son's life. He was a master storyteller and welcomed the opportunity to swap tal
2 CONC es. He was an insightful poet, writing poems laced with humor while being poigna
2 CONC nt and heartfelt.<br><br>Mr. Allison cherished his family. He was never happier 
2 CONC or more content than when he was surrounded by his children, grandchildren, and 
2 CONC great-grandchildren.<br><br>Survivors include nine children, Stephen Allison and
2 CONC  his wife, Diane Hartman, of Fairmount City, Theresa Allison of Wexford, Ruth Cl
2 CONC over of Wilkinsburg, Pa, David Allison and Dalena McCauley Rupp of South Bethleh
2 CONC em, Linda Allison-Doane and her husband, Ron, of Horseheads, N.Y., Kenneth Allis
2 CONC on and his wife, Dawna, of Fairmount City, Thomas Allison of Clearfield, Susan A
2 CONC llison and her husband, Patrick Koeppl, of Limestone, and Tate Allison and his w
2 CONC ife, Rebecca, of Fisher; 20 grandchildren; 20 great-grandchildren; and a large e
2 CONC xtended family including numerous nieces, nephews and friends.<br><br>He is also
2 CONC  survived by his sister, Yvonne Stewart of Xenia, Ohio; a brother-in-law, Edgar 
2 CONC Shofestall, of Corsica; a brother-in-law, Robert Reinsel, and his wife, Bernice,
2 CONC  of Fairfax, Va.; and a brother-in-law, Ed Reinsel, and his wife, Edie, of Fairf
2 CONC ax, Va.<br><br>Mr. Allison was preceded in death by his beloved and cherished wi
2 CONC fe, Peggy; his parents; infant son, John; his sister, Patricia Shofestall; his b
2 CONC rother, Lee Allison; a sister-in-law, Susanne Miller; a brother-in-law, Rudolph 
2 CONC Miller; a and brother-in-law, Robert Stewart.<br><br>The Allison family wishes t
2 CONC o thank Diana and Janianne Patton who have provided unending love and care for B
2 CONC ob over the past three and a half years. Their dedication and compassion have co
2 CONC mforted not only Bob and Peggy, but the entire family. The Allison family will b
2 CONC e forever grateful for them and to all of the caregivers who enriched the lives 
2 CONC of Bob and Peggy.<br><br>The family will receive friends from 4 to 8 p.m. on Fri
2 CONC day, November 1, at the Alcorn Funeral Home in Hawthorn.<br><br>A memorial servi
2 CONC ce will be held at the Limestone Fire Hall on Saturday, November 2, 2019 at noon
2 CONC  to celebrate and remember Mr. Allison's life.<br><br>At the luncheon service, f
2 CONC amily and friends are encouraged to share favorite stories and thoughts of Bob.<
2 CONC br><br>Memorial donations can be made in Mr. Allison's name to the Clarion Fores
2 CONC t VNA, 271 Perkins Road, Clarion, PA 16214 and/or a .<br><br>Visit www.alcornfun
2 CONC eralhome.com to share a memory or leave a condolence.<br>Published in The Leader
2 CONC  Vindicator from Oct. 28 to Nov. 7, 2019
