2 CONC years by the Daughters of the American Revolution organization.  In order to fin
2 CONC d his grave, walk north toward I-80 from the narrow dirt road.  His grave is und
2 CONC er a very large oak tree in the cemetery and has a US Flag adornment.  A word of
2 CONC  caution…when you are leaving the cemetery, be very careful when entering Route 
2 CONC 66.  The field of vision is quite limited from both directions and cars sometime
2 CONC s speed through that area.<br><br>   <br> <br><br>Tate Allison, of the third gen
2 CONC eration, was married to Mary Calhoun.  They are buried in Limestone Cemetery, wh
2 CONC ich is located in Limestone, PA (Clarion County).  Tate Allison lived from 1801 
2 CONC (some data reads 1807) to ?? and Mary Calhoun lived from 1805 to 1900.  Tate and
2 CONC  Mary had nine children – Samuel, Mary, Sarah, Asenath, Florinda, James B, Charl
2 CONC es, Elizabeth, Robert C.<br>I was unable to locate Tate and Mary’s gravesites, b
2 CONC ut there does appear to be a family plot area in a corner of the cemetery.  Perh
