2 CONC and, William Mercer.<br><br>  <br><br>ALLISON ANCESTRAL GRAVES OF CLARION COUNTY
2 CONC , PA<br><br>If you are looking to visit the gravesites of your ancestors, there 
2 CONC are three cemeteries in Clarion County that are the final resting places for des
2 CONC cendants of Robert Allison.  As you may know, Robert Allison was one of three br
2 CONC others (Andrew, Robert and James) who arrived in America in 1750.  This document
2 CONC  will help you locate the cemeteries where some of our family are buried.<br>Som
2 CONC e of the information in this memo was obtained from a website called FindAGrave.
2 CONC com.  It’s an informative site with ability to search by cemetery and by individ
2 CONC ual name.  In addition, it often has other family members listed, where they are
2 CONC  buried, and brief narratives or obituaries.  <br><br>Robert Allison, one of the
2 CONC  three original brothers, who I will refer to as the first generation, was marri
2 CONC ed to Rebecca (Beckie Beard).  They are buried in Bethel Presbyterian Church Cem
2 CONC etery in Indiana, PA (Indiana County).  Robert Allison lived from 1730 (some dat
