1 NOTE Elizabeth Ann “Betty” Hepfl, 86, of Clarion, passed away early Tuesday morning, 
2 CONC November 20, 2018 at the Clarion Healthcare and Rehabilitation Center.<br>She wa
2 CONC s born on September 15, 1932 in Snydersburg; daughter of the late Arthur and Ida
2 CONC  Ditz Bauer.<br>Betty married Charles Hepfl on August 1, 1951, and he preceded h
2 CONC er in death.<br>She is survived by her children, Linda Summerville and her husba
2 CONC nd Wes of Clarion, Catherine Barr and her husband John of Clarion, Diane Myers a
2 CONC nd her husband Delane of New Bethlehem, James Hepfl and his wife Lynn of Limesto
2 CONC ne, Patricia Girt and her friend Randy Hilliard of Strattanville, Steven Hepfl a
2 CONC nd his wife Michelle of Lamartine, and Donna Smith and her husband Robert of Str
2 CONC attanville, seventeen grandchildren, and eighteen great grandchildren.<br>Betty 
2 CONC was a homemaker and she also worked for many years on the Highland Township Elec
2 CONC tion Board.<br>She was a member of the Immaculate Conception Catholic Church in 
2 CONC Clarion, where she was part of the Ladies Guild.<br>Betty enjoyed family gatheri
2 CONC ngs and cooking for the family.<br>She also enjoyed quilting and meeting with he
2 CONC r friends for lunch to share and discuss quilting projects.<br>Betty loved plant
2 CONC ing large gardens and taking care of her flowers.<br>She is also survived by her
2 CONC  siblings, Edith Reinsel and her husband Ed of Virginia, Joseph Bauer and his wi
2 CONC fe Mary of Ohio, Marie Mauersburg of Clarion, Bernice Reinsel and her husband Ro
2 CONC bert of Virginia, Mike Bauer and his wife Nancy of Clarion, Evelyn Dwyer of Ohio
2 CONC , Jane Lander of Oil City, Dan Bauer and his wife Wendy of Maryland, and Ray Bau
2 CONC er and his wife Diane of Lucinda.<br>Betty was preceded in death by her parents,
2 CONC  husband, her infant twin brother, and her infant sister.<br>Betty’s family will
2 CONC  receive friends from 2 p.m. to 4 p.m. and 6 p.m. to 8 p.m. on Friday, November 
2 CONC 23, 2018 at the Robert V. Burns Funeral Home in Clarion.<br>Mass of Christian Bu
2 CONC rial will be celebrated at Noon on Saturday, November 24, 2018 at the Immaculate
2 CONC  Conception Catholic Church with Rev. Monty Sayers, presiding.<br>Interment will
2 CONC  follow in the Immaculate Conception Catholic Cemetery.<br>In Lieu of flowers, d
2 CONC onations can be made in Betty’s name to the Community Action Agency, 38 S Sherid
2 CONC an Rd, Clarion, PA 16214.<br><br><br>To send flowers or a memorial gift to the f
2 CONC amily of Elizabeth A. Hepfl please visit our Sympathy Store.
