1 NOTE Jane Doris Lander, 79, of Oil City, died peacefully Wednesday, October 27, 2021,
2 CONC  surrounded by her family.<br>Jane was born September 9, 1942, in Lucinda, and w
2 CONC as the daughter of the late Arthur Leo and Ida (Dietz) Bauer of Lucinda.<br><br>
2 CONC On Jan. 19, 1963, Jane was married to Arthur Joseph Lander who preceded her in d
2 CONC eath.<br><br>Jane was a member of St. Stephen Church (now St. Joseph Parish). Sh
2 CONC e also participated in the YMCA water aerobics class, where she made many good f
2 CONC riends.<br><br>Jane’s greatest love was her family.<br><br>Her home was always o
2 CONC pen and her happiest moments were spent surrounded by family making meals, doing
2 CONC  crafts, puzzling and playing Euchre or Chinese checkers together.<br><br>Her fu
2 CONC ll and meaningful life is reflected in fond and loving memories of time spent to
2 CONC gether with her children, grandchildren and great-grandchildren.<br><br>Her fami
2 CONC ly will always cherish the memories of card tournaments, handmade quilts created
2 CONC  for each family member, and her beautiful gardens and the pond in Lancaster.<br
2 CONC ><br>Jane owned JanLanArts, a quilting and floral business in Lucinda for many y
2 CONC ears. When she and Art moved to Lancaster, she moved the business to Ephrata. Ar
2 CONC t and Jane returned home to Western Pennsylvania after both retiring.<br><br>Jan
2 CONC e is survived by her three daughters: Christine A. Snyder and her husband Neal o
2 CONC f San Antonio, Texas, Mary E. Loll and her husband Bernie of Seneca, and Michell
2 CONC e C. Lander of Oil City; and her two sons: Patrick A. Lander and his wife Robin 
2 CONC of Oil City, and Arthur J. Lander, Jr. and his wife Megan of Lancaster.<br><br>S
2 CONC he is also survived by eight grandchildren, Connor Snyder, Lauren Snyder, Audrey
2 CONC  Snyder, Garret Snyder, Erica McGuire, Justin Loll, Suart Lander and Colleen Sny
2 CONC der, and four great-grandchildren, Jace Loll, Austyn Loll, Finley Snyder and Jon
2 CONC athan McGuire.<br><br>She is also survived by her siblings, Edith Reinsel (Ed) o
2 CONC f Virginia, Marie Mauersburg of Clarion, Bernice Reinsel (Robert) of Virginia, M
2 CONC ike Bauer (Nancy) of Clarion, Evelyn Dwyer of Ohio, Dan Bauer (Wendy) of North C
2 CONC arolina, and Ray Bauer (Diane) of Lucinda.<br><br>In addition to her parents and
2 CONC  husband, she was preceded in death by her brother, Joseph Bauer; and her sister
2 CONC , Betty Hepfl.<br><br>Visitation for friends and family will be held Friday (Oct
2 CONC . 29) from 4 – 7 p.m. in Hile-Best Funeral Home, 2781 Rte. 257 in Seneca.<br><br
2 CONC >Mass of Christian Burial will be held Saturday (Oct. 30) at 11 a.m. in St. Step
2 CONC hen Catholic Church, 21 State Street in Oil City, with Father Johnathan Schmolt,
2 CONC  parochial vicar, as celebrant.<br><br>Interment will follow in St. Joseph Cemet
2 CONC ery in Lucinda, Clarion County.<br><br>Memorial contributions may be made to the
2 CONC  Kirtland Cancer Foundation, P.O. Box 108, Franklin, PA 16323.
