1 NOTE Joseph A. Bauer 1934-2019<br>Obituaries<br><br>Jul 17, 2019<br><br>HOWLAND — Jos
2 CONC eph A. Bauer, 84, of Howland, entered into rest on Sunday evening, July 14, 2019
2 CONC , at Concord Health Care Center.<br><br>He was born Nov. 26, 1934, in Lucinda, P
2 CONC a., a son of Arthur and Ida Ditz Bauer, and moved to Warren in 1955.<br><br>He r
2 CONC etired as a crane operator from Heckett Engineering and was an Army veteran. He 
2 CONC was a member of St. Thomas the Apostle Church in Vienna.<br><br>Besides his wife
2 CONC , the former Mary Ann Mauersberg, whom he married in 1959, he leaves two sons, R
2 CONC andall J. of Newport, Mich. and Clifton M. of Middletown; a daughter, Laurie O’L
2 CONC eary of Franklin, Tenn.; three brothers, Raymond of Lucinda, Pa., Mike of Clario
2 CONC n, Pa. and Daniel of Baltimore, Md.; five sisters, Edith Reinsel and Bernice Rei
2 CONC nsel, both of Fairfax, Va., Marie Mauersburg of Clarion, Pa., Evelyn Dwyer of Ca
2 CONC nfield and Jane Lander of Oil City, Pa.; and two grandchildren.<br><br>Besides h
2 CONC is parents, a sister, Betty Hepfl, is deceased.<br><br>A Mass of Christian buria
2 CONC l will be 10:30 a.m. Thursday, July18, 2019, at St. Thomas the Apostle Church, 4
2 CONC 453 Warren Sharon Road, Vienna, Ohio, where the family will receive friends one 
2 CONC hour prior. Officiating will be the Rev. Frank Zanni. Burial will follow in All 
2 CONC Souls Cemetery in Bazetta.<br><br>Arrangements have been entrusted to the care o
2 CONC f the Staton-Borowski Funeral Home, 962 North Road NE, Warren, Ohio 44483, 330-3
2 CONC 94-6200. Dedicated to serving your loved ones.
