1 NOTE Obituary<br>A Mass of Christian Burial will be held 10 AM Wednesday at St. Micha
2 CONC el Catholic Church for Thomas J. Dwyer, 78, of Canfield who passed away Sunday A
2 CONC pril 19, 2015 at Humility House. Tom was born August 13, 1936 in New Bethlehem, 
2 CONC PA. son of the late Thomas P. and Ruth (Clinger) Dwyer and came to the area in 1
2 CONC 966. He retired from the General Motors Lordstown maintenance department, in 200
2 CONC 0 after more than 30 years of service. Tom was a member of the church, and the S
2 CONC t. Michael's Men's Club. He was also involved with Barbershop singing for 48 yea
2 CONC rs most recently with the Stephen Foster Chorus in Warren for the past 20 years.
2 CONC  Tom was a jack of all trades and could fix almost anything. He also enjoyed tra
2 CONC veling, and loved watching and investing in the stock market, and was always wil
2 CONC ling to give investment advice. Most of all, Tom enjoyed spending time with his 
2 CONC grandchildren and attending their sporting events. Tom leaves his wife the forme
2 CONC r Evelyn "Cookie" Bauer, whom he married June 23, 1962, three children, Tom (Sha
2 CONC ron) Dwyer of Cincinnati, Jim Dwyer of Washington DC, and Barb (Dave) Nicholson 
2 CONC of Richfield, four grandchildren, Bryce and Chad Nicholson, Anne and Tommy Dwyer
2 CONC . Tom also leaves five siblings, Leona Dunkle and Helen Reed, both of Clarion, P
2 CONC A, Jerry Dwyer and Eileen Himes, both of New Bethlehem, PA, and Fran Seymour of 
2 CONC Medina, OH. Besides his parents, Tom was preceded in death by two sisters, Ruth 
2 CONC Kemer and Mary Kennedy and one brother, John Dwyer. Friends may call from 4 to 7
2 CONC  PM April 21th at the Lane Family Funeral Home, Canfield Chapel where closing pr
2 CONC ayers will be held at 9:30 AM on Wednesday,April 22nd, prior to the mass at the 
2 CONC church. In lieu of flowers, the family suggests donations be made to Hospice of 
2 CONC the Valley or to Blast Glioblastoma Cancer Research @ www.blastgbm.com in Tom's 
2 CONC name.
