2 CONC ied Mary Magdalen _____ Oct 29 1762<br>Johannes Eck and his sons,Joseph and Joh 
2 CONC n, served in the 7th CompanyBerks County Militia duringthe Revolutionary War. Th
2 CONC ere were part of alarge group of men who had tooccasionally miss days of mili ta
2 CONC ry serviceand consequently had to pay anexercise fine.  The men who paid thes ef
2 CONC ines were known as exercise menand were not the same asnon-associators, men w ho
2 CONC  never shouldered a gunor recognized the fightfor freedom.  These exercise me n 
2 CONC were in actualmilitary service duringthe years of 1776, 1777, and 1778.  Some ti
2 CONC mes thepressing needs of thefarm were such that they had to leave their military
2 CONC  duties for shortperiods of time to fulfill their family obligationsand it w as 
2 CONC better topay a fine than to neglect their families.  John Eckand his sonsful fil
2 CONC led their military duties rather well because theywere among thegroup of men tha
2 CONC t paid the smallest fines.<br><br>MoreAbout JOHANNES (JOHN) EGG:<br>Fact 1: 23 M
