1 NOTE The history of the Fescenmyer family begins in Germany. <br>Records from Germany
2 CONC  were obtained by Art Faller, a <br>descendant of Jacob Fasenmyer, son of Casper
2 CONC . Those <br>records show the following information: <br>Peter Fescenmayer was bo
2 CONC rn July 27, 1681. Died Feb. 24, <br>1722. He was married to Eva Andres. <br>Pete
2 CONC r had a son Mathias Fasenmayer - born -. married- <br>Jan 21, 1737 and died Oct.
2 CONC  1767. He was married to Maria <br>Mayer - born 1712, died Oct. 20, 1781. <br>Ma
2 CONC thias had a son Balthasar Fesenmayer - born Dec. 31, <br>1754. Married Feb. 1784
2 CONC  and died May 10, 1794. He was <br>married to Maria Barbara Beck. They had a son
2 CONC : <br>Balthasar Fesenmayer - born Jan. 1, 1787 and married <br>March 3, 1817. He
2 CONC  maried Maria (Agatha) Bierer. born <br>Jan 23, 1797. This is the Baltzer Fasenm
2 CONC yer (English <br>spelling) that came to America in 1828 and settled in <br>Washi
2 CONC ngton twp. Clarion County. - Fryburg, Pa. This <br>Balthasar (Baltzer) had a bro
2 CONC ther named Alois <br>Fesenmier (German spelling). Alois had a son named <br>Balt
2 CONC zer also. <br>The information on this Baltzer is found in the back <br>section o
2 CONC f this book. His descendants settled around <br>the New Bethlehem, Pa. area.
