1 NAME Edward John /Gormley/
1 SEX M
1 BIRT
2 DATE Sep 14 1931
1 NOTE Passed away peacefully, surrounded by loved ones, on July 20, 2018, at age 86. B
2 CONC rother of the late Mary Joan Gormley. Beloved husband for 50 years of the late M
2 CONC arion Gormley. Devoted partner of Millie Tohey. Cherished father of Joan Gormley
2 CONC  (VA), Marian Gormley (VA), Paul Gormley (CT), and Jerome Gormley (CA). Loving g
2 CONC randfather of Jennifer, Jamie, Jake and Tara. Great-grandfather of Zion, Zeke, H
2 CONC azel, and the late Orion. Edward was born in McKees Rocks to Edward Gormley Sr. 
2 CONC and Jane Reinsel Gormley. He was employed in the HVAC field at Johnson Controls 
2 CONC Company and Robertshaw Controls. He operated his own company, SPECS Inc., as an 
2 CONC HVAC engineer. Edward was devoted to his family, his 50-year marriage to Marion,
2 CONC  and his service in the U.S. Army during the Korean Conflict. Family and friends
2 CONC  will be received at Laughlin Cremation and Funeral Tributes 222 Washington Rd. 
2 CONC Mt. Lebanon, PA 15216. on Monday July 23, 2-4 p.m. and 5-8 p.m. Mass of Christia
2 CONC n Burial  will be offered in St. Winifred Church, Tuesday morning, at 10:30 a.m.
2 CONC (Everyone Please Meet at Church) Interment will follow at Christ Our Redeemer Ce
2 CONC metery (North Side Catholic Cemetery).
