1 NOTE OBIT<br>Florence T. (Haberberger) Copello(1928 - 2017)<br>Florence T. Copello, 8
2 CONC 9, a resident of Pinecrest Manor and formerly of 241 Dippold Ave., St. Marys, di
2 CONC ed Thursday, Sept. 7, 2017 at Penn Highlands Elk after a lengthy illness.<br>She
2 CONC  was born Feb. 22, 1928 in St. Marys, daughter of the late Edward and Helen Baue
2 CONC r Haberberger. She was a lifelong resident of the area and was a graduate of Cen
2 CONC tral Catholic High School, Class of 1945.<br>On June 29, 1946 in the St. Mary's 
2 CONC Church, Florence married Maurice O. "Mouse" Copello, who preceded her in death M
2 CONC arch 26, 2006.<br>Florence was a member of the St. Mary's Church. She enjoyed pl
2 CONC aying bingo and cards and taking trips to Salamanca.<br>She is survived by two d
2 CONC aughters, Linda Brown and her husband Bradley of Mansfield and Marjorie Timm and
2 CONC  her husband Mark of St. Marys; a son, Thomas E. Copello and his wife Ruth of Ca
2 CONC mbridge Springs; six grandchildren, Eric Brown, Erin Brown, Brian Copello, Laura
2 CONC  Dandoy, Carrie Dulay and Daniel Timm; 10 great-grandchildren; and by a brother,
2 CONC  Arthur Haberberger and his wife Joanne of Reading.<br>In addition to her husban
2 CONC d and parents, Florence was preceded in death by a sister, Dorothy Walker.<br>A 
2 CONC Mass of Christian Burial for Florence T. Copello will be celebrated in the St. M
2 CONC ary's Church on Saturday, Sept. 9 at noon with the Rev. Peter Augustine Pierjok,
2 CONC  OSB, pastor, officiating. Burial will follow in the St. Mary's Cemetery.<br>Vis
2 CONC itation is at the Lynch-Radkowski Funeral Home on Friday, Sept. 8 from 6-8 p.m.<
2 CONC br>Memorials, if desired, may be made to the Christian Food Bank, P.O. Box 1033,
2 CONC  St. Marys, Pa. 15857, or to the St. Mary's Church, 325 Church St., St. Marys, P
2 CONC a. 15857.
