1 NOTE William Hense left his home in Centralia when he was about 16 andafterworking<b 
2 CONC r>during the summer in Nachez, Washington he returned toMinnesota. He cameto<br 
2 CONC >Crow Lake with a man by the name of Moffet. Heobtained work with a fineman by< 
2 CONC br>the name of Leslie Jack and in the country school house of Crow Wing he met h
2 CONC is future wife, Anna Belle Wilson. After working for Leslie Jack, William Hense 
2 CONC found work inthe Northern Pacific Car Shops and went to Board at the Wilson home
2 CONC .Later becoming an apprentice in the machine shops, finishing his apprenticeship
2 CONC   after his marriage to Anna >Belle. The had three daughters,Jesse Anna, Verna L
2 CONC elia and Lillian Jean.In<br>1910 William Moved His family to Tacoma , Washington
2 CONC . He transferred to Port Angles as a Round House foreman in 1919. He retired at 
2 CONC 63 years old because of<br>ill health.
