1 NOTE John Kuhn and his family arrived on the ship Marlbourough, ThomasBellCapitan<br 
2 CONC >from Rotterdam but last from Cowes. Sept. 23, 1741. JohnKuhn was acarpenter<br 
2 CONC >with whom the Rev. Theodore Schneider the founderof the GoshenhoppenMission.<b 
2 CONC r>He is reported to have built the firstCapel at Goshenhoppen.    Name:  	Johann
2 CONC es Kuhn  Year: 	1741   	America  Family Members:   	Son Johannes 23;   Son Johan
2 CONC n Wilhelm 13  Source Publication Code: 	4145  Primary Immigrant: 	Kuhn, Anna Eli
2 CONC sabetha  Annotation: 	Emigrants to America in the 18th century from the area of 
2 CONC the Duchy of Zweibruecken, according to records in the state archives at Speyer.
2 CONC  Names 36 emigrants, 1728-1776, with places of origin, some ages, family data, d
2 CONC estinations in America, and some date  Source Bibliography: 	KREBS, FRIEDRICH. "
2 CONC Amerika-Auswanderer des 18. Jahrhunderts aus dem Gebiet des Herzogtums Zweibruec
2 CONC ken: aus den Akten des Staatsarchivs Speyer." In Genealogie, vol. 10:2 (Feb. 197
2 CONC 0), pp. 50-53.  Page: 	50
