1 NOTE Obituary for Arthur Joseph Lander<br>Arthur Joseph Lander, 73, of Oil City, died
2 CONC , Friday, September 19, 2014, at UPMC Mercy Hospital in Pittsburgh, surrounded b
2 CONC y his family.<br>Born June 3, 1941 in Lucinda, he was a son of the late Joseph B
2 CONC . and Loretta Schupp Lander.<br>Arthur served honorably in the US Marine Corps.<
2 CONC br>He was a self-employed carpenter for many years and finished his career as a 
2 CONC construction supervisor, working for the Horst Group in Lancaster, PA until his 
2 CONC retirement in 2006.<br>Mr. Lander was a member of St. Stephen Church as well as 
2 CONC a member of the Knights of Columbus.<br>Arthur’s great love was his family. He e
2 CONC njoyed spending time with his children and grandchildren. He was always generous
2 CONC  with his time and carpentry skills, helping his family with many home improveme
2 CONC nt projects.<br>On January 19, 1963 he married the former Jane Bauer, who surviv
2 CONC es.<br>In addition to his wife, Arthur is survived by two sons, Patrick A. Lande
2 CONC r and his wife Robin of Oil City, and Arthur J. Lander, Jr. and his wife Megan o
2 CONC f Lancaster; three daughters, Christine A. Snyder and her husband Neally of San 
2 CONC Antonio, TX, Mary E. Loll and her husband Bernard of Seneca, and Michelle C. Lan
2 CONC der of Oil City; and eight grandchildren, Erica Loll, Justin Loll, Stuart Lander
2 CONC , Colleen Lander, Connor Snyder, Lauren Snyder, Audrey Snyder, and Garrett Snyde
2 CONC r.<br>Also surviving are two brothers, Ralph Lander of Fryburg, and Russell Land
2 CONC er of Clarion; one sister, Bernice Beirnik of Erie; and numerous nieces and neph
2 CONC ews.<br>In addition to his parents, he was preceded in death by eight sisters, S
2 CONC usan Marie Dayton, Grace Zacherl, Bernadine Goughler, Helen Lander, Florence Sch
2 CONC mader, Catherine Whitehill, Beatrice Biltz and Ann Kinch; and three brothers, Da
2 CONC niel Joseph Lander and twins Frederick and Paul Lander who died at birth.<br>Fri
2 CONC ends may call at the Morrison Funeral Home on Sunday from 2-4 pm and 7-9 pm.<br>
2 CONC A Mass of Christian Burial will be celebrated at 11 am Monday in St. Stephen Chu
2 CONC rch with the Rev. Matthew Ruyechan, pastor, presiding.<br>Interment will be in S
2 CONC t. Joseph’s Cemetery, Lucinda.
