1 NOTE Catherine G. Reinsel, 98, of Lancaster, PA, formerly from Clarion, PA, died peac
2 CONC efully at Lancaster General Hospital on Saturday, December 12, 2015.<br><br>Born
2 CONC  in Parkers Landing, PA, she was the widow of Donald J. Reinsel who passed away 
2 CONC in 1973. She was the daughter of the late Frederick A. and Anna Mae Crate Markle
2 CONC y.<br><br>Catherine was a faithful member of St. John Neumann Catholic Church an
2 CONC d was a former member of St. Philip’s and St. Leo The Great Catholic Church. She
2 CONC  was a member of the Millersville Senior Citizen’s Club. Her greatest love was h
2 CONC er family and she loved spending time with her grand and great grandchildren. Sh
2 CONC e will be remembered as a caring and simple woman, and enjoyed taking in relativ
2 CONC es when in need, as well as being the family babysitter.<br><br>She is survived 
2 CONC by her two daughters, Rita M., wife of William J. Jordan and Maryann K., wife of
2 CONC  Robert C. Palmer, all of Lancaster; 9 grandchildren and 18 great grandchildren.
2 CONC  She is also survived by two sisters, Theresa Fritz, St. Mary’s PA and Beatrice 
2 CONC “Bea” Waite, Bear Rocks, PA.<br><br>Relatives and friends are invited to attend 
2 CONC the Mass of Christian Burial from St. Nicholas Catholic Church, 3028 Shannondale
2 CONC  Road, Mayport, PA 16240 on Saturday, December 19, 2015 at 12:00 Noon with The R
2 CONC ev. Samuel Bungo Celebrant. Interment at St. Nicholas Catholic Cemetery. Kindly 
2 CONC omit flowers. Memorial contributions may be sent to the church.
