1 NOTE Mary Ann Bauer, 80, formerly of Warren, Ohio passed away Thursday, November 4, 2
2 CONC 021, at Hospice of Butler and Warren County, Middletown, Ohio.  She was born on 
2 CONC February 7, 1941 in Sigel, PA. to William and Hazel Mauersberg.  She was married
2 CONC  for 59 years to the late Joseph A. Bauer. Mary was a retired guidance counselor
2 CONC  at Warren G. Harding High School and held various teaching positions at Warren 
2 CONC Ohio City Schools.  She served on the Howland School Board in the late 70’s.  Sh
2 CONC e was preceded in death by 2 sisters and 5 brothers and is survived by two sons,
2 CONC  Randall of Newport, MI, Clifton (Melissa) of Middletown, OH, daughter Laurie O’
2 CONC Leary (Jeff) of Franklin, TN, and grandchildren Levi (Clifton) and Melanie (Laur
2 CONC ie). In Lieu of Flowers, the family requests donations to Hospice of Butler and 
2 CONC Warren Counties or The Alzheimer’s Association. Memorial mass will be held at Al
2 CONC l Souls Cemetery, Cortland, Ohio on Monday, November 8, 2021 at 1:00 with Father
2 CONC  Kopp officiating. Visitation will be from 12:00 – 1:00 p.m. at the chapel in Al
2 CONC l Souls Cemetery. Condolences may be sent to the family at www.bakerstevensparra
2 CONC more.com.
