1 NOTE Charles R. McGarrity, 82  05/19/2010  email this storyEmail to a friendpost a co
2 CONC mmentPost a Commentprinter friendlyPrinter-friendly  Charles R. McGarrity, 82, o
2 CONC f Oak Ridge, died suddenly on Thursday evening, May 13, 2010, at Brookville Hosp
2 CONC ital.  Born August 31, 1927, in Oak Ridge, he was the son of Thomas and Marie (H
2 CONC etrick) McGarrity.  He married Phyllis J. Kube on May 29, 1952. She preceded him
2 CONC  in death on July 29, 1998.  Mr. McGarrity served with the United States Army du
2 CONC ring the end of World War II.  He worked as a parts salesman for Willison`s GM G
2 CONC arage in New Bethlehem.  Mr. McGarrity was a member of the Oak Ridge United Meth
2 CONC odist Church.  Survivors include a son, Daniel C. McGarrity of Oak Ridge; two gr
2 CONC andchildren, Jonathan and Danielle McGarrity of Eddyville; a brother, James McGa
2 CONC rrity of Brackenridge; two sisters, Betty Thomas of Hawthorn and Rose Kube of Oa
2 CONC k Ridge; and numerous nieces and nephews.  In addition to his parents and wife, 
2 CONC he was preceded in death by a son, Joseph J. McGarrity; four brothers, John, Tom
2 CONC , Robert and Dale McGarrity; and two sisters, Helen Miles and Ilene McAninch.  F
2 CONC uneral services were held at 2 p.m. on Sunday, May 16, 2010, at the Alcorn Funer
2 CONC al Home in Hawthorn with lay leader and niece, Carol (McGarrity) Brown, officiat
2 CONC ing.  Interment was in Mount Zion Cemetery, Mahoning Township, Armstrong County.
