2 CONC  moved to this<br>community.<br><br>Deceased is sursvived by 3 sons and 4 daught
2 CONC ers: Thomas, at home; John, Vandergrift; Bernard, Pittsburgh; Mrs. John Ryan, Cl
2 CONC eveland; Mrs. John Grogan, Pittsburgh, and Mrs. Boyd Kammerdeiner, of Goheenvill
2 CONC e.<br><br>She is also survived by one sister, Mrs. Patrick Carr, Philadelphia, a
2 CONC nd by 19 grandchildren. Two daughters, Anna and Margaret, preceded her in death.
2 CONC <br><br>Funeral services in her memory were held in the St. Charles church on Fr
2 CONC iday, July 14, at 10 o'clock, and were conducted by Father Daniel Fitzpatrick of
2 CONC  Reynoldsville.<br><br>Interment under the direction of R. F. Mateer & Son was m
2 CONC ade in the St. Charles cemetery at this place.<br><br>This obit was listed in th
2 CONC e newspaper in New Bethlehem, Clarion county, Pennsylvania, US<br><br><br>Bernar
2 CONC d Immigrated to Philadelphia in 1881 He and Mary were married there, but there i
2 CONC s no date of the marriage. at the port of entry, the immigration clerk changed t
2 CONC he name from McGrenaghan to McGranahan. On Bernard`s death certificate[ 1929} th
2 CONC e name is Actually spelled Mcgrannithan as is his father's  name on the same cer
2 CONC tificate.
