1 NOTE <a>Susanna`s mother died when Susanna was 2 years old and Susanna was moved from
2 CONC  home to home. She lived for a while with an Aunt in Barnsboro and later with An
2 CONC thony (Mike) and Lucy Reinsel McGarrity. When she was 14 she kept house for her 
2 CONC uncle Bob and helped raise Mary, Anthony`s daughter. Later she worked in Frankli
2 CONC n for the Judge as a house keeper.She then moved back to New Bethlehem and worke
2 CONC d in Hepler`s Drug store. It was while she worked there that she met Bob.  They 
2 CONC married when Susanna was 24 and Bob was 25, on October 27, 1926. As a grandchild
2 CONC  of Susan Owens and Thomas McGarrity, Susanna was suppose to receive $100 at the
2 CONC  age of 16. This was a bequest for being a namesake.However, due to a lawyers er
2 CONC ror, Susanna never received the bequest.</a><br><br>      McGranahan—•Reinsel _ 
2 CONC   .<br>• On Wednesday morning. October 27, 1926, at 9:00 o'clock, in St.Charles 
2 CONC Catholic Church, New Bethle-<br>hem, Miss Susanna McGranahan, daughter of Michae
2 CONC l McGranahan and Robert Reinsel, son of Mr. and<br>Mrs. Ed Reinsel of Crates, we
2 CONC re united in marriage by the Rev. Father F J. Graves. The bride wore white<br> s
2 CONC atin and carried a shower boquet of  white roses and lilles Of the valley.  Miss
2 CONC  Marcella Reinsel, who was<br> bridesmaid, wore a gown of blue  and carried whit
2 CONC e roses. Thomas Carlos, of New Bethlehem, served as Mr.  Reinsel's bestman. ' Fo
2 CONC llowing the  ceremony the couple motored to<br> Crates where the wedding dinner 
2 CONC was  served. Mr. and Mrs. Reinsel left this  week on a motor trip. They will vis
2 CONC it<br> in Youngstown, Ohio, and may include  Detroit in their itinerary.She was 
2 CONC born February 14, 1902, in New Bethlehem, the daughter of Bernard Michael and Su
2 CONC san McGarrity McGranahan. She was married to Robert D. Reinsel who preceded her 
2 CONC in death.<br>Mrs. Reinsel was a member of the St. Nicholas Church, Crates. Survi
2 CONC ving are: two sons, Edward I. Reinsel of Camp Springs, Md., and Robert D. Reinse
2 CONC l of Fairfax, Va. ; two daughters, Mrs. Rudolph (Susanne) Miller of Girard, and 
2 CONC Mrs. Robert C. (Margaret) Allison of Fairmount City RD 1; and 22 grandchildren.<
2 CONC br>Funeral services will be held Thursday, Dec. 7, 1972, at 10 a.m. at the St. N
2 CONC icholas Church, Crates, with the Rev. Edward Bula, officiating. Interment will b
2 CONC e in the St. Nicholas Cemetery, Crates.
