1 NOTE One of the brothers involved in the assassination of William Sydney Clenents.<br
2 CONC ><br>Bernard McGranahan, a son of Thomas and Mary (Friel) McGranahan, was  born 
2 CONC in November 1853, and died at his home in Porter township, near  Leisure Run Roa
2 CONC d, about two miles north of town, on Thursday, May 16,  1929, aged 76 years and 
2 CONC 6 months. The cause of his death was heart trouble.  Mr. McGranahan was a coal m
2 CONC iner and lived a quiet, contented life,  honored and respected by all who knew h
2 CONC im. He was a consistent member of  the St. Charles Catholic Church of this place
2 CONC , and on Monday of this  week at 9 o`clock, services in the church in his memory
2 CONC  were conducted  by his pastor, Rev. Father F. P. Shields. Interment under the d
2 CONC irection  of R. F. Mateer was made in the St. Charles cemetery.  He is survived 
2 CONC by three sons and four daughters, namely, Thomas, John,  Bernard, Catherine, Mar
2 CONC y, Grace and Marjory.    This was listed in the New Bethlehem newspaper  New Bet
2 CONC hlehem, Clarion county, PA, US    <br>On his death the name is spelled McGrannit
2 CONC han.
