1 NAME Daniel Thomas /Miller/
1 SEX M
1 BIRT
2 DATE Jul 05 1948
1 DEAT
2 DATE Jan 09 2012
2 PLAC Erie PA
1 NOTE Obituary  Daniel T. Miller    |   Visit Guest Book    Daniel T. Miller, 63, of M
2 CONC illcreek, died on Monday, January 9, 2012 at the VA Medical Center in Erie. Dan 
2 CONC was born July 5,1948 at the National Naval Medical Center in Bethesda, Md., a so
2 CONC n of Rudolph L. and Mary Susanne Miller of Girard. He attended St. John`s Grade 
2 CONC School and graduated from the Girard High School in 1967. He later attended the 
2 CONC Behrend Campus of Penn State University in Erie. In 1968 he enlisted in the U.S.
2 CONC  Army, where he was later deployed to Vietnam and served as a medical X-Ray Tech
2 CONC nician. He served two tours of duty in Vietnam and was awarded the Vietnam Servi
2 CONC ce Medal, the Bronze Star Medal, the Republic of Vietnam Campaign Medal, with 60
2 CONC  device, the Good Conduct medal and three overseas bars. Upon his discharge from
2 CONC  the military he returned to the Erie area and went to work for Zurn Industries 
2 CONC as an X-Ray Tech in manufacturing. He also worked at Avanti`s Restaurant and mos
2 CONC t recently had been employed by Presque Isle Beer 4 Less. He loved the job as we
2 CONC ll as the customers and friends he made working there. He was a member of the Sp
2 CONC ortsmen`s Athletic Club of Millcreek, enjoyed sports, especially boxing, and lov
2 CONC ed going to Casinos where he played craps and poker. He appreciated all types of
2 CONC  music, especially the music of the 60`s, riding roller coasters with his daught
2 CONC er, motorcycling and having a cold beer with friends. He was preceded in death b
2 CONC y a sister Kathleen (Miller) Roberts. Survivors include his loving parents; daug
2 CONC hter, Carly (Miller) Vanta and her husband Jeffrey of San Antonio, Texas; a sist
2 CONC er Rosanne (Miller) Joseph and her husband Michael of Kingwood, Texas; brother-i
2 CONC n-law Dennis Roberts and his wife Christine of Fairview, Pa.; his former wife bu
2 CONC t life long soulmate, Ann L. Miller of Millcreek; his close friend, Leeann Goodw
2 CONC in of Millcreek; eight nephews, one niece and many friends. Many thanks to a spe
2 CONC cial angel, Julie Ninkovic, RN, whose advice and compassion helped make his last
2 CONC  year, as Dan said, "the best year of my life." Also thank you to the 5th floor 
2 CONC hospice staff at the VA, the staff at the Cancer Center and the many friends who
2 CONC  came to visit. In accordance with his wishes, Dan`s body will be donated to sci
2 CONC ence. There will be no calling hours observed. A Celebration of His Life will be
2 CONC  held on his birthday July 5, 2012 at Camp Sherwin, at a time to be announced. I
2 CONC n lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Meals on Wheels, 1128 State Street, 
2 CONC Suite 317, Erie, PA 16501, where he volunteered for many years. Funeral Arrangem
2 CONC ents are under the direction of Daniel R. Edder Funeral Home, Girard. To send co
2 CONC ndolences visit edderfuneralhome.com    Published in the Erie Times-News on Janu
2 CONC ary 11, 2012
