1 NAME Rudolph LaVern /Miller/
1 SEX M
1 BIRT
2 DATE Dec 01 1927
1 DEAT
2 DATE Jan 07 2014
2 PLAC Girard, PA
1 NOTE Rudolph L. Miller, 86 of Girard, passed away Tuesday, January 7, 2014 at the Vet
2 CONC erans Affairs Medical Center.<br><br>He was born on December 1, 1927 to the late
2 CONC  Frank I. and Anne Mae Songer Miller in Brookville, Pa.  Rudolph graduated from 
2 CONC Clarion-Limestone High School with the class of 1945 where he attended school wi
2 CONC th his lifelong sweetheart. Following graduation, at the age of 17, he enlisted 
2 CONC in the US Navy during WWII. In 1948 he was discharged and joined the reserves. H
2 CONC e then went to Erie Business College where he earned his associates degree. Duri
2 CONC ng the Korean War he was called back to active duty, where he served in Port Lya
2 CONC utey, in French Morocco for 18 months. He then returned back to Girard, and bega
2 CONC n working at Marx Toys until he began his life career as a meat cutter. Rudolph 
2 CONC worked for Platz's Grocery store and later Brown Brothers in Girard for more tha
2 CONC n 25 years. <br><br>Rudy was very pleased to be from the little village of Shann
2 CONC ondale, Pa. and just as pleased to be a part of the Girard community for many ye
2 CONC ars.   As a boy, he spent summers and his high school years with his cousins on 
2 CONC "the farm."  His sister's husband Ritchie exposed him to his livelong passion of
2 CONC  hunting and fishing.  He shared wonderful times with his family and Girard frie
2 CONC nds at "Camp Burp," his hunting camp in Tionesta. Pa.  His retirement years allo
2 CONC wed him to "winter" in Florida for 15 years.  Rudy loved to dance, tell jokes an
2 CONC d sing and enjoyed the visits and fun times with his many friends of all ages.<b
2 CONC r>  <br>Rudolph was a member of St. John the Evangelist Roman Catholic Church in
2 CONC  Girard. He was a member of the church choir, the Knights of Columbus (4th), was
2 CONC  a past Grand Knight, and Knight of the Year. Rudolph was a Boy Scout leader for
2 CONC  many years and a member of the Girard American Legion, Post #494.<br><br>In add
2 CONC ition to his parents, he was preceded in death by two children, his daughter Kat
2 CONC hleen Roberts and his son Daniel Miller; three sisters, Gladys Ritchey, Grace Ha
2 CONC uge and Virginia King; and his brother Woodrow Miller.<br><br>He will be deeply 
2 CONC missed by his wife of 66 years, Mary Susanne (Reinsel) Miller. He also leaves be
2 CONC hind his daughter Rosanne Joseph and her husband Michael of Houston, TX; a daugh
2 CONC ter-in-law, Ann Miller of Millcreek, a son-in-law, Dennis Roberts and his wife C
2 CONC hristine of Fairview; ten grandchildren and four great grandchildren.<br><br>Fri
2 CONC ends may call on Friday from 2-4 and 6-8 PM at Edder Funeral Home, Inc., 309 Mai
2 CONC n St. East, Girard. A Prayer Service will be held there on Saturday at 9:30 AM f
2 CONC ollowed by the Funeral Mass at 10 AM at St. John the Evangelist Catholic Church,
2 CONC  101 Olin Ave., Girard.<br><br>Burial with full military honors will be in St. J
2 CONC ohn's Cemetery.
