1 NOTE Anna Virginia Reinsel Ross, 87 of 1212 Chestnut St. Franklin, passed away on Sat
2 CONC urday evening, March 16, 2013.<br><br>Born in Clarion on July 5, 1925 she was a 
2 CONC daughter of the late Norbert and Anna Josephine Cyphert Reinsel.<br><br>She was 
2 CONC a graduate of Clarion High School.<br><br>Mrs. Ross enjoyed embroidering and rea
2 CONC ding and loved spending time with children and her family.<br><br>She was of Cat
2 CONC holic faith.<br><br>In 1950 she married Thomas Ross and he preceded her in death
2 CONC  in 1989.<br><br>Surviving is a sister in law, Antoinette Reinsel of Oil City; 1
2 CONC 0 nieces and nephews, Ruth Reinsel of Long Island, Mary Ellen Reinsel of VT, Mar
2 CONC garet Dady of Chicago, Greg Reinsel and his wife Vicky of CA, Rick Reinsel and h
2 CONC is wife Joan of FL, Cindy Gurnee and her husband Ray of Franklin, Dan Reinsel an
2 CONC d his wife Julie of Franklin, Elsie Mae and Betty Lou of Brackenridge and Karen 
2 CONC Malvaro of Butler.<br><br>Also surviving are numerous great nieces and great nep
2 CONC hews who she treasured and many friends at Colonial Manor.<br><br>She was preced
2 CONC ed in death by a sister Amber Henry; three brothers, Glenn Reinsel, Norbert Rein
2 CONC sel, and Cletus Reinsel; a sister in law, Lee Reinsel; a brother in law, Charles
2 CONC  Henry and two nephews Robert Reinsel and Bill Henry.<br><br>Family and Friends 
2 CONC welcome Friday from 11:00 – 12:00 P.M. at Huff Funeral Home & Cremation Services
2 CONC  Inc. 312 West Park St. Franklin.<br><br>Funeral services will be held at 12:00 
2 CONC P.M. Friday in the funeral home with Deacon Walter Jones of St. Patrick Church a
2 CONC nd Rev. David Foote of the Franklin Baptist Temple, officiating.<br><br>Intermen
2 CONC t will follow at Immaculate Conception Cemetery in Clarion.
