1 NOTE Henry and Elizabeth Reinsel had a son, Anthony, baptized Oct 1801 or 1802.His sp
2 CONC onsors were John Orendorf and Magdalene [Aloine] Orendorf.The Orendorfs were mar
2 CONC ried July 12, 1795 at Reading, according to the Goshenhoppen Register (page 181)
2 CONC . <br>     The birth records in Lebanon show that this Anthony Reinsel was a bro
2 CONC ther  of John H. Reinsel. His children would have been first cousins of the Rein
2 CONC sel brothers of Crates. Antony`s name is spelled numerous ways in both church an
2 CONC d county records.<br>     Anthony Reinsel or Rensel married Elizabeth Hanlin, No
2 CONC v.6, 1821.Anthony Reinsel and Elizabeth Hanlin were sponsors of John Reinsel son
2 CONC  of Conrad Reinsel on March 25, 1821, six months before Anthony married. Anthony
2 CONC  Rensel and Elizabeth Hanlin`s children were:<br>Joseph born Sept. 22, 1822.  Jo
2 CONC seph married Nancy Cyphert daughterof Anthony Cyphert son of Philip II.<br>     
2 CONC George born  31 July 1824 died 6 Feb 1910.  George married Susanna Clara Aaron.<
2 CONC br> William born 1827 (1827-1895) married Catherine Brinkley<br>     Dennis born
2 CONC  1829<br>Sarah born 1832<br>     Elizabeth born 1835<br>     Catherine born 1838
2 CONC <br>     Mary born 1841<br><br>     As an aside, the above William Ransel who al
2 CONC so appears on page 541 of  The Aarons of Crates, married to Catherine Brinkley, 
2 CONC  is one of Tom Dwyer`s ancestors.  Note also that Thomas Aaron`s daughter marrie
2 CONC d a Brinkley.<br>     The 1830 Census of Pennsylvania, Westmoreland County ( pag
2 CONC e 168) Roll 164. Shows this Anthony Rancil living in Derry Township, Westmorelan
2 CONC d County with 3 males less than 5, 2 males - 5 and less than 10, 1 male -10and l
2 CONC ess than 15, 1 male-  30 and less than 40<br>During the mid 1800's Anthony's fam
2 CONC ily lived near Corsica, PA<br>     The 1880 Census shows Anthony living with his
2 CONC  Daughter Catharine Sweeney in Oil City, PA.<br>The census shows that his father
2 CONC  (Henry) was born in Germany.
