1 NOTE Charles M. Reinsel, 84, Tilden Township, died in the Laurel Center, Tilden Towns
2 CONC hip, where he had resided the past year.    He was the husband of Edith L. (Sund
2 CONC ay) Reinsel, who died Jan. 25, 1997. They were married Aug. 19, 1950.    Charles
2 CONC  was born in Tilden Township and was the son of the late Clarence D. and Mollie 
2 CONC M. (Miller) Reinsel.    Charles and his wife were the owners and operators of th
2 CONC e Reinsel Dairy Farm in Tilden Township for 37 years, retiring in 1988. During h
2 CONC is farming years, Charles was a farm produce huckster in Reading. After retiring
2 CONC  from the farm, he was a cattle weigh-in clerk for the Leesport Auction for seve
2 CONC ral years.    He was a 1943 graduate of Hamburg High School.    He was a member 
2 CONC of St. Michael`s Church, Tilden Township, as well as St. Michael`s Sunday School
2 CONC , his entire life. Charles served the church as a former church councilman and w
2 CONC as a former member of St. Michael`s Cemetery board.    He was a life member of t
2 CONC he Shartlesville Grange and a 60-year member of Vaux Lodge 406 F&AM, Hamburg, wh
2 CONC ere he achieved the 32nd degree.    Charles is survived by two daughters, Faye M
2 CONC ., wife of Thomas Werley Jr., Tilden Township, and Ruth C. Reinsel, Temple; and 
2 CONC one grandson, Steven C. Werley.    Funeral services will be held on Wednesday at
2 CONC  11 a.m. from St. Michael`s Church, Tilden Township, with a viewing from 10 to 1
2 CONC 1 a.m. in the church. A viewing will also be held on Tuesday from 7 to 8:30 p.m.
2 CONC  in the Burkey & Driscoll Funeral Home Inc., 40 S. 4th St., Hamburg. Masonic ser
2 CONC vices will begin at 8 p.m. Burial will be in St. Michael`s Cemetery, Tilden Town
2 CONC ship.    In lieu of flowers, contributions may be made to the memorial fund of S
2 CONC t. Michael`s Church or St. Michael`s Cemetery at 529 St. Michaels Road, Hamburg,
2 CONC  PA 19526.
