1 NOTE Conrad was born in 1791 (per Reinsel Prayer book) and the Census.Some records sh
2 CONC ow this Conrad`s birth date as 1795). Conrad married Susan Hanlin (b:1797) on Au
2 CONC gust 26, 1817.<br>This Conrad Reinsel orRansel of the third generation was born 
2 CONC in 1791(perhaps 1795) accordingto the Reinsel prayer book. He married Susan Hanl
2 CONC in August 26, 1817. They had ten children. The baptisms of three of these appear
2 CONC  in the Baptisms of Western Pennsylvania:<br>     Catherine born July 16, 1816 b
2 CONC aptized Aug.2;<br>     Mary born Sept. 30, 1818 baptized Oct. 30; and<br>     Jo
2 CONC hn born Jan. 28, 1821. The sponsors of John were Anthony Reintzel and his wife.<
2 CONC b r><br> The Census of 1830, roll 164 page 169 shows this Conrad Rancil living i
2 CONC n Derry Township<br>Westmoreland County His household consisted of: 1 male < 5, 
2 CONC 1 m ale 5 <10, 1 male 20 < 30, 2 males 30 < 40,2 females < 5, 2 females  5 < 10,
2 CONC  2f emales 10 < 15, 1 female 30 <40<br>This appears to be 2 families with one of
2 CONC  the mothers missing.<br><br>The 1850 Census of Derry Township, Westmorland Coun
2 CONC ty shows Conrad Reinsele age 55 as a shoemaker. Note the age is likely wrong.He 
2 CONC was probably 59. His wife was Susan Reinsele age 53 -- born 1797.Their children 
2 CONC were:<br>     Catherine born July 16, 1816 Baptized Aug2.<br>     Mary born Sept
2 CONC  3 0 1818 Baptized Oct. 30<br>     John born Jan28 1821. His sponsors were Antho
2 CONC ny Reintzel and his wife<br>     Melinda Reinsele 27 born 1823<br>     Henry Rei
2 CONC nse le age 22 born 1828 -<br>died 1895 -Buried at St. Martin`s Church, New Derry
2 CONC ,Westmorland County<br>     Sara Reinsele age 20 born 1830<br>     Thomas Reinse
2 CONC le age19 born 1831<br>     Rosan Reinsele age 17 born 1833<br>     Ann Reinsele 
2 CONC age 15 born 1835<br>     Agnus Reinsele age 12 born 1838<br><br>Descendants of t
2 CONC his family are numerous and widely distributed across the United States. For the
2 CONC  most part they spell their name Ransel or Ransil.Much of the following material
2 CONC  was provided by John Ross Ransil,  Bernard J. Ransil, and Leonard Ransil. <br>
