1 NOTE Son of Henry Reinsel. Older brother of John H.Reinsel and Anthony. Aunt Cora`s r
2 CONC ecord is the only historical evidenceof the relationship of John H. and Daniel R
2 CONC einsel. He married Elizabeth Seifert and they had five sons and one daughter. He
2 CONC  and his sister Rachel were  sponsors at a  baptism in Westmoreland county in 18
2 CONC 10. He was killed by lightening in 1822 and left his wife with six very young ch
2 CONC ildren. His estate was worth about $300 when he died. His children were 2 months
2 CONC  to seven years old in 1922.  Daniel`s birthday is not recorded.  Part of his fa
2 CONC mily is documented in Bill Reinsel`s book,The Reinsel`s of Pennsylvania. We know
2 CONC  that Daniel Reinsel and Rachel Reinsel (brother and sister) were sponsors of Jo
2 CONC hn Casali at his baptism on 6/17/1804. This is recorded in St. Mary Church in Le
2 CONC banon. Daniel Reinsel died in 1822, 4 years before his brother John married. Dan
2 CONC iel`s oldest child, Joseph, was 9 when Daniel died. Assuming that Daniel and Eli
2 CONC zabeth Seifert were married in 1812 and he was 20 or more when he was married he
2 CONC  was probably born prior to 1792. The evidence fo rthis is also strengthened by 
2 CONC the fact that he was a baptism sponsor in 1804 along with his sister, so he was 
2 CONC probably 16 or 17 years old at thetime. Also, he was old enough to stay behind w
2 CONC hen Henry moved to Westmoreland County in 1804 or 1805.   Daniel`s daughter, Ann
2 CONC a(Hannah) Reinsel, was born 6/30/1815 (Page249 Goshenhoppen Reg.) and died 7/16/
2 CONC 1890.  She was the second child of Daniel Reinsel and Elizabeth Seifert Reinsel.
2 CONC  Her  sponsors at baptism were James and Mary Arentz. This James and Mary were l
2 CONC ikely the uncle and aunt of Margaret Arents, John H.Reinsel`s wife. Anna was mar
2 CONC ried to Jacob Arentz born  12/31/1809 died12/25/1887. Jacob was most likely a co
2 CONC usin of Margaret Arentz.
