1 NOTE Edward Ignatius Reinsel`s wife Margaret Ann Aaron was the daughter of Jacob Aaro
2 CONC n who was the son of Joseph Aaron, Daniel Aaron`s brother. Thus Ed and Margaret 
2 CONC were second cousins.  Having grown up on adjacent farms and married, they purcha
2 CONC sed a farm of 106 acres in Redbank Township, Clarion County, Pennsylvania. Until
2 CONC  abo ut 1913, they lived in a log cabin on the farm and this is where they raise
2 CONC d their 13 children.At age 57 or 58 Ed built a new house of tile blocks, glazed 
2 CONC a dark brown, and put a slate roof on the house. In about 1928, Edward and Marga
2 CONC ret and their daughter Marcella moved to Crates and lived in the house up the ro
2 CONC ad from the church. Their son Bob and his wife Susanna moved from Crates to the 
2 CONC farm. Ed never really adjusted to the move away from the farm.  During the three
2 CONC  years till his death, Ed often came to the farm and stayed with Bob and Susanna
2 CONC .  Susanna often said that Ed Reinsel was a true gentleman.
