2 CONC at baptism were John Flour and Anna Mary Flour.John H. Reinsel may have been nam
2 CONC ed after his sponsor John Henry Flour. We can only speculate as to why it took a
2 CONC  year to have John Baptized. Perhaps there was no priest in the area or they liv
2 CONC ed far from a church. John H. married Margaret Arents in 1826 when she was 18 ye
2 CONC ars old. Witnesses at the Wedding of John H. Reinsel and Margaret Arents Reinsel
2 CONC  were George Arents Sr. (her father) and James Byrne.  The marriage is recorded 
2 CONC on page 5, Marriages 1819-1846, as recorded in Baptisms Antiquus. The baptismal 
2 CONC records at St. Mary`s church begin in 1797, the year before John is baptized and
2 CONC  are discontinued for a period of about 20 years after 1810. Therefore, the reco
2 CONC rd does not include that of his children except for the solemn communion of Pete
2 CONC r, John`s youngest son. The Flower or Flour family was still living in the Readi
2 CONC ng area in 1807 because they had a son James baptized there.  John Henry Flower 
2 CONC was born in March 1771, of Henry Flower and his wife. He was baptized at Reading
2 CONC , May 12, 1771. His sponsors were John Grett and ______ Flower.  Note that John 
2 CONC Flour and Anna Mary, his wife moved west and appear in the Baptisms of Western P
2 CONC ennsylvania. John Flour died April 20, 1819 at the age of 49. See Page 99, Bapti
2 CONC sms of Western Pennsylvania. His two year old son, Daniel, born Sept 9, 1816 die
2 CONC d April 21, 1819. Flowers still live near Derry in Westmoreland County.<br>Accor
2 CONC ding to Cora Reinsel Slattery, John H. Reinsel`s granddaughter, John was the son
2 CONC  of George Reinsel. This seems to have been a mistake unless he was called Georg
2 CONC e Henry Reinsel. It is interesting to note that one of Cora`s great grandfathers
2 CONC  was George Adam Arents.  Perhaps there was some confusion as to which great gra
2 CONC ndfather was named George. <br>John H. Reinsel lived in Jackson Township in Leba
2 CONC non County in 830, according to the census.  He also lived in E. Hanover Townshi
2 CONC p in 1840. It has been said that John was born near Myerstown in Lebanon County.
2 CONC  We know that he moved to Clarion County about 1849 to 1850. He owned afarm in n
2 CONC ortheastern Limestone Township in the early 1850s.  John H. Reinsel married Marg
2 CONC aret Arentz in 1826.  She would have been 18 years old at the time of their marr
2 CONC iage and John would have been 29.    The 1830 Census of Jackson Township, Lebano
2 CONC n County shows John Reintzel as head of household for a family of 1 male 30-40, 
2 CONC 2 males less than 5 (Jonathan 3 years and Levi), one female 20-30. That census a
2 CONC lso shows Elizabeth Reintzel as the head of household with 1 female 40-50 1femal
2 CONC e 15-20 one male 10-15, 1 male 5-10 this woman is obviously Daniels widow. In th
2 CONC e 1840 Census of East Hanover Township, Lebanon County, John Reinsel is the head
2 CONC  of household with, 1 male less than 5, Peter; 1 male 30-40, himself; 1 female 2
2 CONC 0-30, his wife Margaret; 1 female 5-10, Elizebeth; and 2 females less than 5, Ma
2 CONC ry and Rebecca. In the 1850 Census John (Rensell)and His family are shown living
2 CONC  in Clover Twp, Jefferson County, But his farm was actually in Limestone TWp Cla
2 CONC rion County. His property value was listed as $800. He was Identified as a farme
2 CONC r. The people in his household were listed as John 55, Margaret 40, Rebecca 18,P
2 CONC eter 16, Elizabeth 14, Polly 12, John 8, Louisann 6 month, (I suspect that this 
2 CONC is really Roseanna)   <br>St. Mary`s Church, Lebanon,Pa.Microfilm at Lebanon His
2 CONC torical Society. John Reintzel born 24 June 1797 son of Henry and Elizabeth Rein
2 CONC tzel    Sponsors,John Flour and Anna Marie Flour.
