1 NOTE Obituary for Louise R. Shiffer<br>March 1\<br><br>Louise R. Shiffer, of Warminst
2 CONC er and formerly of Willow Grove, passed away into God's loving care on Saturday,
2 CONC  August 24, 2019. She was 94 years old. Louise was born on March 18, 1925 in Phi
2 CONC ladelphia to the late George and Pauline (née Ness) Reinsel. She was the wife to
2 CONC  the former Pastor at Holy Trinity Evangelical Lutheran Church in Abington, Rev.
2 CONC  Alvin O. Shiffer, D.D. who served as Pastor there from 1952 to 1986. Together t
2 CONC hey shared 54 years of marriage until he passed away in 2000.<br><br>Louise was 
2 CONC a graduate of Olney High School and was active with her husband in his vocation 
2 CONC as Pastor of Holy Trinity in Abington. She was a member of the church choir and 
2 CONC was active in the Holy Trinity Lutheran Church Women's Group and assisted in man
2 CONC y other responsibilities with her husband in the church. In her free time, she e
2 CONC njoyed vacationing with her family to their shore home in Brigantine, N.J. Louis
2 CONC e was also very artistic and enjoyed drawing and painting. She used her artistic
2 CONC  talent each year making her own Christmas cards to send to her family and frien
2 CONC ds.<br><br>Louise is survived by her three children; Eric G. Shiffer (Starr), Ma
2 CONC rk A. Shiffer (Candace), Amy S. Fittery (William) as well as three grandchildren
2 CONC ; Mark (Kara), Steven (Stephanie), Thomas and three great grandchildren; Mackenz
2 CONC ie, Leah, and Dylan. She is predeceased by her brother, Robert Reinsel and survi
2 CONC ved by her sister in law, Claire.<br><br>Relatives and friends are invited to Lo
2 CONC uise's Life Celebration on Friday, September 6, 2019 from 10:00-11:30 a.m. at Ho
2 CONC ly Trinity Evangelical Lutheran Church, 2086 Parkview Ave. Abington, PA 19001 fo
2 CONC llowed by her funeral service at 11:30 a.m. Interment will follow at Whitemarsh 
2 CONC Memorial Park. Parking will be available at the entrances of Craft-Givnish of Ab
2 CONC ington, Inc. located at Old York Rd. and Old Welsh Rd.<br><br>Memorial contribut
2 CONC ions in Louise's name may be made to either the church at the above address or S
2 CONC ilver Springs Martin Luther School at www.silver-springs.org. Family services ar
2 CONC e entrusted under the care of Craft-Givnish of Abington, Inc., 215-659-2000.
