1 NOTE December 13, 1917  Margaret E., wife of William Weaver, of Redbank Township, ans
2 CONC wered the last great call on Thursday morning, Dec. 6, 1917, aged 60 years.  She
2 CONC  had been in poor health for some time and the end was not unexpected.  She was 
2 CONC the daughter of Janathan and Rosanna Reinsel and was born on a farm adjoining th
2 CONC e home where she died.  She was married to William Weaver in 1885 at St. Nichola
2 CONC s Church at Crates, at the same place where was baptized and where her funeral s
2 CONC ervices were held.  Her husband and seven children survice her, viz. J.B. Weaver
2 CONC , of Ford City; Walter at Camp Lee, Virginia; Edward J., in the aviation corps, 
2 CONC at Nashville, Tenn; Mary, wife of Leason George, of Limestone township, Clyde, R
2 CONC ose and Leona at home.  She was one of a large family and her brothers, Ed of Re
2 CONC dbank township; D.L., of Limestone township; J.T. Weaver, Esq, of Clarion, and h
2 CONC er sisters Mrs. John Aaron, of Meadville; Mrs. P.F. Fiscus, of Porter township; 
2 CONC Mrs. William Fiscus, of Apollo, and Cora and Emma on the old homestead were all 
2 CONC able to attend the funeral services which were conducted by Rev. Father Fitzgera
2 CONC ld on Monday morning last.  Her two sons who are volunteers under the stars and 
2 CONC stripes were able to be present at the last obsequies which united the whole sor
2 CONC rowing family. She was a good and conscientious wife and mother and a kind neigh
2 CONC bor and was always ready to lend a helping hand to any one in need. May she rest
2 CONC  in peace.
