1 NOTE View Sign<br><br>Mary "Susanne" (Reinsel) Miller, passed away peacefully, surrou
2 CONC nded by her family on Monday August 8, 2016 at Westlake Woods.<br><br>She was bo
2 CONC rn on August 29, 1927 in Brookville, Pa. to the late Robert and Susanna (McGrana
2 CONC han) Reinsel.<br><br>Susanne was raised and educated in Redbank Twp. and graduat
2 CONC ed from Clarion-Limestone High School in 1945. After her husband was discharged 
2 CONC from the military, their family moved to Girard. She worked 26 years at Platz an
2 CONC d later Brown Brothers Grocery store as a clerk. After retiring she and her husb
2 CONC and wintered for 15 years in Fla.<br><br>Susanne was an active member of St. Joh
2 CONC n the Evangelist Roman Catholic Church in Girard. She was a Eucharistic minister
2 CONC , a lectern and designer of the quilts for St. John's Bazaars. She coordinated m
2 CONC ultiple Clarion-Limestone class reunions, participated for many years in the nei
2 CONC ghborhood card club, was a Girl Scout leader, and volunteered at Pleasant Ridge 
2 CONC Manor. She was an excellent homemaker that hosted and added such special touches
2 CONC  to so many holiday gatherings. She enjoyed crosswords, reading biographies, fam
2 CONC ily genealogy research, cooking, sewing, ceramics, painting, and social gatherin
2 CONC gs (especially the annual Labor Day weekend at "Camp Burp".)<br><br>In addition 
2 CONC to her parents she was preceded in death in 2014 by her husband, Rudolph L. Mill
2 CONC er, whom she married on August 20, 1947; her daughter, Kathleen Roberts; and her
2 CONC  son, Daniel Miller.<br><br>She will be greatly missed by her family which inclu
2 CONC de her daughter, Rosanne Joseph and her husband Michael of Crosby, Texas and rec
2 CONC ently, Edinboro, Pa.; her son-in-law, Dennis Roberts and his wife Christine of F
2 CONC airview; her daughter-in-law, Ann Miller of Millcreek; her sister, Margaret Alli
2 CONC son and her husband Robert of Clarion, Pa.; her brothers, Edward Reinsel and his
2 CONC  wife Edith, and Robert Reinsel and his wife Bernice, all of Fairfax, Va.; ten g
2 CONC randchildren; Carly Vanta (Jeff); Paul Roberts (Colene); Chris Thompson,; Michae
2 CONC l Joseph (Elisa); Nick Joseph (Anne); Brad Thompson (Shaunna); Amber Farris (Mat
2 CONC t); Trevor Roberts (Chelsey): Gregory Roberts; and Tyler Joseph and four great-g
2 CONC randchildren, Miracle, Berkley, Ty and Camden.<br><br>Friends may call on Thursd
2 CONC ay from 2-4pm and 6-8pm at Edder Funeral Home, Inc., 309 Main St. East, in Girar
2 CONC d. A Prayer Service will be held there on Friday at 9:30am followed by the Funer
2 CONC al Mass at St. John the Evangelist Catholic Church, 101 Olin Ave., Girard at 10a
2 CONC m.<br><br>Burial will be in St. John's Cemetery.<br><br>Memorials may be made to
2 CONC  St. John the Evangelist Roman Catholic Parish Center, 101 Olin Ave., Girard, PA
2 CONC  16417.<br><br>To send condolences visit edderfuneralhome.com<br><br>Sign the Gu
2 CONC estbook at www.GoErie.com/obits<br><br><br><br>Funeral Home<br>Edder Funeral Hom
2 CONC e<br>309 Main Street<br>Girard, PA 16417<br>(814) 774-4306<br>Funeral Home Detai
