2 CONC on Sunday October 18, 2015. Born September 13, 1927, in Moon Township, son of th
2 CONC e late Andrew R. and Eugenia (McLaughlin) Reinsel. Beloved husband of 60 years t
2 CONC o Alice (Freithofer) Reinsel; father of Ruth (David) Hollifield of Moon Twp., Th
2 CONC omas (Karen) Reinsel of Sewickley and Timothy Reinsel of Coraopolis; grandfather
2 CONC  of Jamie (Chris) Hinkle, Kelly (Chad) Giger, Matthew (Amanda) Hollifield and Ka
2 CONC te (Tim) Carl; great-grandfather of Logan and AJ Hinkle; brother of the late Est
2 CONC her Adriano, John, Fred, James and Norbert Reinsel. Paul was an Army veteran of 
2 CONC World War II, a member of St. Joseph's Church where he was an usher, the VFW Pos
2 CONC t 402 and the Knight of Columbus and was a machinist with Homestead Valve. Visit
2 CONC ation COPELAND'S, 867 Fifth Ave. Tuesday 2-4 and 7-9 p.m. Wednesday Mass of Chri
2 CONC stian Burial (TIME) at St. Joseph's Church in Coraopolis. Interment Resurrection
2 CONC  Cemetery with military honors. In lieu of flowers, memorial contributions may b
2 CONC e made to St. Joseph's Church in his memory.<br>Published in Pittsburgh Post-Gaz
2 CONC ette on Oct. 19, 2015
