1 NOTE Peter Reinzel received his first Solomn Communion in March 1847.    Obituary fro
2 CONC m Clarion Democrat 10/18/1900     Peter Reinsel, an aged citizen of Clarion Town
2 CONC ship, died very suddenly at his late residence, Monday morning about eight o`clo
2 CONC ck of heart failure.  Mr. Reinsel was born in Lebanon County in September 1833 a
2 CONC nd at the time of his death was a little over 77 years old.  His wife and ten ch
2 CONC ildren survive him.  They are John, of Redbank Township, Martin of Marienville, 
2 CONC Charles, of Clarion township, Albert, of McDonald`s Corners, Peter, Jr., Fred, a
2 CONC nd Edward who are at home.  Mrs. James A. Aaron, of Limestone township, and two 
2 CONC daughters who are at home.  Three brothers, J.H., Levi, J.A., of Crates and one 
2 CONC sister Mrs. Samuel McAninch of Franklin, also survive him.  The funeral took pla
2 CONC ce Thursday morning at 10:30 at Crates.  Internment in Crates Catholic Cemetery.
2 CONC   Mr. Reinsel was one of the most upright of men, and was universally regarded a
2 CONC s a model husband and father, a good neighbor and progressive citizen.  He was p
2 CONC oor overseer for his township for a great many years, and was not only kind to t
2 CONC he poor, but also careful of the taxpayer`s interest.  His place will not be eas
2 CONC ily filled.  May he rest in peace.
