1 NOTE Richard Kerr Reinsel, 84, of Butler passed away Tuesday at the Lowrie Place in B
2 CONC utler, where he was living.<br>Richard was born June 28, 1932, in Clarion, Pa., 
2 CONC to William Jerome Reinsel and Marie Antoinette Kerr Reinsel. He went to school i
2 CONC n Clarion, graduating from Clarion-Limestone High School. He then served in the 
2 CONC U.S. Army from January 1953 to January 1955 during the Korean War, attaining the
2 CONC  rank of corporal.<br>On Oct. 12, 1957, in Clarion, he married Ruth Clare Heinri
2 CONC ch. She preceded him in death in April 2016.<br>Richard worked for the A&P super
2 CONC market in Clarion for 29 years. In 1988, he retired from AK Steel after 16 years
2 CONC  of employment.<br>A member of St. Paul Roman Catholic Church in Butler, he was 
2 CONC a eucharistic minister and a member of the church choir. He also was an active m
2 CONC ember of the Alhambra Club until failing health forced him to discontinue.<br>Ri
2 CONC chard enjoyed gardening and taught his children when they were young how a veget
2 CONC able plant materializes from a small seed. Those were the best times, he would s
2 CONC ay. He enjoyed reading about world history and the effect it had on America. The
2 CONC  History Channel, the Discovery Channel and Animal Kingdom were his favorite TV 
2 CONC channels.<br>Mr. Reinsel is survived by his three children, Richard K. Reinsel J
2 CONC r. and his wife, Kristy, Diana Lynn "Tory" Bishop and her husband, John "Trent,"
2 CONC  and Eric Lee Reinsel and his wife, Tammy; six grandchildren, Richard K. Reinsel
2 CONC  III, Britney Lauren Webb, Jade Lindsay Bishop, Gabrielle Ruth Bishop, Erica Lyn
2 CONC n Reinsel and Troy Matthew Reinsel; and four great-grandchildren, Rhianna Jade Z
2 CONC endejax, Taylor McKenna Reinsel, Jack Grayson Webb and Maddox Hayes Jones.<br>In
2 CONC  addition, Richard is survived by his sister, Patricia Geary, and her husband, W
2 CONC illiam, of Clarion; his brother, Duane Reinsel, and his wife, Peggy, of Limeston
2 CONC e; and his sisters-in-law and brothers-in-law, Norma Jean Heinrich, Carl Beckwit
2 CONC h, Leona Geraldine (Chris) Heinrich, Maria Philomena (Kookie) Heinrich, Elizabet
2 CONC h Ann (Betty) Keim, Billy Reinsel and Maxine Reinsel.<br>Richard was preceded in
2 CONC  death by his wife; his parents; his stepmother, Ethal F. (Keck) Reinsel; his br
2 CONC others, Cecil Reinsel, Jerome Reinsel Jr. and Cletus Reinsel; his two sisters, M
2 CONC rs. Edward (Helen) Lynch and Mrs. Cameron (Lois) Miller; his granddaughter Arian
2 CONC ne Rene Reinsel; and his sister-in-law, Josephine Reinsel.
