1 NOTE <a>Robert Delmore Reinsel was born in the log cabin on the Ed Reinsel farm. Bob 
2 CONC lived on the farm all his life with brief exceptions. At the age of 13 he fell o
2 CONC ff a log in the woods, breaking his left arm. The arm healed in a permanently be
2 CONC nt shape.  Bob covered the disability so well that many  people never knew he ha
2 CONC d a problem. At the age of 17 he worked for Levi Rhodes as a teamster in Kittann
2 CONC ing. Later he worked on the Ford motor company assembly line in Detroit for 6 mo
2 CONC nths. Also when he and Susanna were first married they lived in the old Convent 
2 CONC Building at Crates until he rented the farm from his father. As a young man he h
2 CONC elped build the electric towers that are on the line from Piney Dam that crosses
2 CONC  the Allison farm. Bob`s mother and his sister Marcella came back to the farm to
2 CONC  live with Bob and Susanna after Ed Reinsel died. When Margaret Aaron Reinsel di
2 CONC ed in 1941, Bob bought the farm from the estate.     In addition to farming, Bob
2 CONC  worked in the gas fields of western Pennsylvania, mostly in Clarion and Armstro
2 CONC ng Counties but at times he roomed and boarded away from home and one winter wor
2 CONC ked as far away as Kane. He was first a tool dresser and then a driller.  He oft
2 CONC en told of walking 5 miles to work at a well, working a 12 hour shift and walkin
2 CONC g home. It was quite common as a youngster to walk 5 miles to Church at Crates o
2 CONC n Sunday morning. He often spoke of walking to Church after he and Susanna were 
2 CONC married. The history of the farm owned by Bob and Susanna Reinsel is as follows:
2 CONC  Originally owned as part of the Broadhead and Thomas Territory in 1785 it was t
2 CONC ransferred to Andrew Porter.1832 to Thomas and Harriet Porter McKean.  1837 to J
2 CONC ohn and Catherine Stahlman.  1861 to Samuel Stewart.  1877 to Chistian and Marga
2 CONC ret Brinker. 1881 to Samuel Aaron. 1884 to Edward I and Margaret Reinsel. 1941 t
2 CONC o Robert D. Reinsel.   1973 to Robert C Allison.
