1 NOTE Verle Adelaide “Midge” Aaron of Clarion, PA, died at age 95, Saturday, October 1
2 CONC 9, 2014.<br><br>She was born on May 5, 1919 in Kingsville, PA and was the daught
2 CONC er of the late Ralph and Rose Reinsel.<br><br>She lived in the Clarion are until
2 CONC  her husband Melvin F. Aaron passed away in 1985. She spent the next 25 years li
2 CONC ving in and loving Florida.<br><br>She traveled to may countries with her family
2 CONC  and loved life. In 2012 she returned to the Clarion area where she lived with h
2 CONC er family. Her passion in life was caring for and helping people.<br><br>She wor
2 CONC ked for many years as a nurse at Brookville Hospital and then Clarion Hospital. 
2 CONC In retirement she cared for family members, volunteered at Clarion Hospital, Mea
2 CONC ls on Wheels, Hospice, and the Catholic Church.<br><br>She is survived by her da
2 CONC ughters, Rosemary Schmader of Norfolk, VA, Martha Aaron and her “hubby” Wally of
2 CONC  Winter Haven, FL, Kathleen Whitney of Raleigh, NC, and sons Melvin Aaron, Jr. a
2 CONC nd wife Robin of Strattanville, PA and Michael Aaron and wife Bonnie of Clarion 
2 CONC PA. She was blessed with 15 grandchildren: Wally Schmader, David Schmader, Lisa 
2 CONC Dixon, Jeff Barger, Shelly Jones, Greg Ransom, Brooke Whitney, Blake Whitney, Ho
2 CONC lly Knotts, Molly Stahlman, Kim Kahle, Steve Aaron, Melanie Armstrong, LeeAnn Pa
2 CONC vlock, and Melvin Aaron, III. She also had 18 great-grandchildren and two great-
2 CONC great-grandchildren. She has two surviving sisters, Jo Pasquerette of Shippenvil
2 CONC le, PA, and Teresa Neuland of Tonawanda NY, and a son-in-law, Dominic Rella of W
2 CONC inter Haven, FL.<br><br>In addition to her husband and parents, she was preceded
2 CONC  in death by her daughter, Loretta Rella, her son-in-law, Walter Schmader, her g
2 CONC reat-granddaughter Devon Knapp, three brothers and three sisters.<br><br>She wen
2 CONC t to her rest after a lifetime of giving. She was love and will be greatly misse
2 CONC d.<br><br>Mass of Christian Burial will be held on Saturday, November 1, at 11:0
2 CONC 0 a.m. at the Immaculate Conception Church in Clarion. Father Monty Sayers will 
2 CONC be officiating.<br><br>Memorial donations may be given in her name to the Clario
2 CONC n-Forest Visiting Nurse Association Hospice (www.cfvna.org) 271 Perkins Rd, Clar
2 CONC ion PA 16214.
