1 NOTE Sue Dotson of Salisbury, MD is a direct descendant of Valentine Reintzel who arr
2 CONC ived in 1738. Her records show that Valentine Reintzel was the first Grand Maste
2 CONC r of the Masonic Lodge of Maryland and as such participated with George Washingt
2 CONC on in the laying of the U.S. Capitol cornerstone in 1793 .<br><br>     There is 
2 CONC a Reintzel family Bible published in 1739 in Basil,Switzerland that is in the Sp
2 CONC ecial Collections Dept. at the Georgetown University Library in DC which lists a
2 CONC ll of the 1738 Valentine`s children, including a Conrad.  Sue Dotson has a copy 
2 CONC of his will. This Valentine of the ship Friendship in 1738 was a son of Johann N
2 CONC icholaus Reintzel and his wife Susanna.<br><br>In the 1739 family Bible, Johan N
2 CONC icholaus Reintzel was listed as having died  Aug 26, 1 769.  He was born  Jan 13
2 CONC , 1674 or 1675  to Susanna Reintzel(MN). Their son, Johan Valentine Reintzel b17
2 CONC 21 was the one who immigrated on the ship Friendship in 1738. Johan Valentine ma
2 CONC rried  Maria Sarah Riegel sometime between 1738 and 1744.Maria Sara Reigle was b
2 CONC orn in 1714 in Pfeffelbach, Rheinland, Prussia. How Maria arrived in Pennsylvani
2 CONC a is unknown.<br><br> Their children were:<br>     1. Andreas (Andrew)Reintzel, 
2 CONC born Oct 18, 1744 w ho married Catherine ______,b abt 1746.<br>2. Maria Elizabet
2 CONC h `Mary` Reintzel born March 25, 1747 Berks   , and died Mar 3, 1832 in Washingt
2 CONC on  DC.  She married John Mountz Sr,born in 1741.<br>     3. Maria Margreta Rein
2 CONC tzel born on March18, 1749, baptized April9th at the St John`s (Host) Reform Chu
2 CONC rch at Tulpehocken.<br>     4. Johan Jacob Reintzel born on  Aug 1, 1751 Jacob R
2 CONC eintzel w ho was baptized, November 16, 1753 at the St. John`s (Host)Reform Chur
2 CONC ch at Tulpehocken,<br>     5. Unknown (page was torn) Reintzel b Aug 6, 1752 d. 
2 CONC Aug 7,  175 2.<br>     6. Conrad Jacob Reintzel born Oct 26, 1753 d. <br>     7.
2 CONC  Johan  b Nov 3, 1755 d. Nov 18, 1828 (He was mayor Georgetown, DC for many year
2 CONC s and had several appointments. by presidents for various positions.) m. Ann Rob
2 CONC ertson Dec 20, 1800.<br>     8. J:Jorg `George`David Reintzel b July 23, 1758<br
2 CONC >     9. Johan Valentine Reintzel Jr., b Feb 26, 1761 d. 1817, m.  Mary Waughop 
2 CONC Feb 25, 1799.  This seems to be his second  marriage but his first is unknown.  
2 CONC His son, Samuel, was SueDotson`s ancestor and h e wasborn prior to 1799.)<br>   
2 CONC   10. Maria Magdalena Reintzel, b March 27, 1763 <br>     11. Maria Katarina Rei
2 CONC ntzel b. March 15, 1765<br>     12. John (Johannes Anthony?) Reintzel b. Jan21, 
2 CONC 1767 m. Elizabeth Waughop 1804.<br><br>     Sue Dotson says<br>`In 1746, Valenti
2 CONC n Reintzel was a trustee for the Blue Mt.(Zion)Reformed Church.<br><br>         
2 CONC  In 1767, Valentine Reintzel paid 6 pounds tax on 100 acres of land and 2 each o
2 CONC f horses, cattle, and sheep. This seems  to be the last record of this family in
2 CONC  PA and all of  the men show up in Prince Georges Co., MD by 1776. <br><br>     
2 CONC      The Reintzel family was very much into real estate .  There are numerous la
2 CONC nd records in the state of Maryland for this family.  They were active in the de
2 CONC velopment of Georgetown, DC and are mentioned in many of the historical accounts
2 CONC  of Georgetown as having made donations of land for the church, money to build t
2 CONC he M Street Bridge, etc. and both Valentine of 1761 and Daniel were quite active
2 CONC  in the Masons and local government.`<br><br>          Sue Dot son`s direct line
2 CONC  is as follows:  Johan Nicholaus Reintzel,  Johan Valentine Reintzel Sr., Johan 
2 CONC Valentine Reintzel Jr.,Samuel Reintzel b. abt 1784 DC m. Amelia Ball,William Hen
2 CONC ry  Reintzel b.1827 DC m. Elizabeth Ansea Faulkner, Charles Henry Faulkner Reint
2 CONC zel b.1857 DC m. Anne Elizabeth Collins, Edna Ellen Reintzel b . 1899 m. Ernest 
2 CONC Bernard Wrenn  Sr., Ernest Bernard Wrenn Jr.b. 1921 m. Dorothy Ruth Ross,  Susan
2 CONC  Elizabeth Wrenn (me) b. 1954 m.Phillip Howard Dotson.  Sue and Philip have two 
2 CONC children, Craig Curtis Ross Dotson b. 1979 and Cynthia Jean Dotson b. 1981. `<br
2 CONC ><br>      Itseems that Jacob above settled in York County, Pennsylvania.  In th
