1 NOTE Arrived on the Ship Speedwell Sept. Sept 25. 1749. Captain James Creagh. Adam Se
2 CONC ifert arrived on the Ship Fane Oct 17,1749.Jost Wilhem Rentzel and Johann Heinri
2 CONC ck Rentzel arrived on the same ship. The Aarons of Crates by Paul and Catherine 
2 CONC Shannon shows Philip as being from Alsase Loraine. A letter fo r George M Seifer
2 CONC t (grandfather of Daivd Seifert) states that he and his brothers were from Holle
2 CONC rn Zollern Seven other Seiferts arrived between 1752 and 1774  Jim Cyphert says:
2 CONC  I have a handwritten letter by my greatgrand father George M. Seifert in which 
2 CONC he states the following:`Johannes Cyphert is supposed to have emigrated from Hol
2 CONC lern Zollern,or Baden, Germany sometime in the years 1740-1748 and is supposed t
2 CONC o be demptionist and landed in Phila. and was hired on a farm in the lowerpart o
2 CONC f Bucks County (PA)....... and that two brothers should have emigrated two years
2 CONC  later by the names of Adam and Phillip, one settled in Warren County, NJ and th
2 CONC e other in Berks County, this state.... of which we know nothing about.  Also, t
2 CONC he following from a handwritten note at the bottom of the Seifert Family Tree pr
2 CONC oduced for the annual Seifert Reunion in 1906 by a now deceased person:  `John S
2 CONC iford supposedly emigrated from Gross Horillin in Germany and landed in Philadel
2 CONC phia.... his two brothers Adam and Phillip emigrated two years later, one settle
2 CONC d in Berks County, PA and one in Warren County,NJ.
