1 NOTE Sister Lois Ann Yeaney, 83: Newspaper Obituary and Death Notice  Erie Times-News
2 CONC  (PA) - May 10, 1996  Deceased Name: Sister Lois Ann Yeaney, 83  Taught in Erie 
2 CONC and area diocesan schools    Sister Lois Ann Yeaney, 83, of the Sisters of Saint
2 CONC  Joseph, died    Thursday, May 9, 1996, in her 55th year of religious life.    S
2 CONC he was born in Akron, Ohio, Nov. 22, 1912, daughter of the late    Hasper and Lo
2 CONC is Reinsel Yeaney.    She entered the congregation in 1941 from St. Vincent Pari
2 CONC sh,    Akron, made profession in 1946 and celebrated her Golden Jubilee in    19
2 CONC 91.    A graduate of Villa Maria College, she worked for library    certificatio
2 CONC n at Penn State-Behrend and Edinboro universities. She was    a housemother at t
2 CONC he former St. Joseph Home for Chidlren and taught in    diocesan schools in Mead
2 CONC ville, Clearfield, Ridgway and Erie.    At the Sister`s Community Living Center,
2 CONC  she did clerical work    before entering the prayer ministry in Marycrest.    S
2 CONC he was preceded in death by two brothers, Robert and Edward Yeaney.    She is su
2 CONC rvived by her religious community, the Marycrest staff and    distant relatives.
2 CONC     Friends may call at the Villa Maria Community Living Center, 5031    West Ri
2 CONC dge Road, today from 3 p.m. until a prayer service begins at 7    p.m. A Mass of
2 CONC  Christian Burial will be celebrated there Saturday at 9    a.m. Burial will be 
2 CONC at Calvary Cemetery.
